  "prompt": "Which are the best institutes in Germany for masters in automotive engineering?",
  "response": "Germany is renowned for its strong engineering programs, particularly in automotive engineering. Some of the top institutes for pursuing a master's degree in automotive engineering in Germany include:\n\n1. **Technische Universit\u00e4t M\u00fcnchen (TUM)** - TUM offers a Master's in Automotive Engineering and is known for its excellence in research and collaboration with industry leaders.\n\n2. **RWTH Aachen University** - A highly respected university with an internationally recognized Master's program in Automotive Engineering. RWTH Aachen is noted for its research facilities and strong industry connections.\n\n3. **Karlsruhe Institute of Technology (KIT)** - KIT provides advanced courses and research opportunities in automotive engineering, benefiting from its partnerships with top automotive companies.\n\n4. **Technische Universit\u00e4t Berlin (TU Berlin)** - TU Berlin offers specialized Master's programs with a focus on innovation and sustainable automotive technologies.\n\n5. **Technische Universit\u00e4t Braunschweig** - Known for its strong emphasis on practical and experimental approaches in automotive engineering, TU Braunschweig offers comprehensive Master\u2019s programs in the field.\n\n6. **University of Stuttgart** - Offers a Master's in Automotive and Engine Technology, with a focus on combining traditional automotive engineering with innovative, future-oriented topics.\n\n7. **Technische Universit\u00e4t Dortmund** - Provides advanced training and research in automotive systems engineering, emphasizing both theoretical and application-oriented approaches.\n\nThese universities are recognized for their strong academic programs, advanced research opportunities, and close ties with the automotive industry. It is always advisable to check specific program details, faculty expertise, and industry connections when choosing the right institute for your master's degree.",
